result.execSummary:
The defendant David T Julius was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft by Contractor (fr. Person/Corpse), a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 779.02(5).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Follow through with AODA treatment/counseling if deemed appropriate by Agent.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription. Comply with random urine screens.  Maintain absolute sobriety.

No contact with victim.  Defendant to forfeit the construction trailer and all of it's contents to the victim.  Defendant not to work as a general contractor.  Court would consider lifting this condition if defendant attends appropriate schooling.
  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
  If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.

Defendant David T Julius in court with attorney Matthew Huppertz.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney David Wanta appeared for the victim. Parties stipulate to restitution amount of $80,153.41.  ADA Galaviz advises the District Attorney's office is currently holding $11,700.00 that was paid by the defendant.  Court orders the money being held by the District Attorney's office to be released to the victim immediately.  Court passes matter to read letters for sentencing.  Case recalled at 10:25.  Recommendations by the State.  Statement by victim.  Arguments by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.  

Court orders the following:
- Sentence withheld
- 5 years Probation CONCURRENT with current Extended Supervision 
- Court costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Restitution in the amount of $68,453.41 to be paid to the victim as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Defendant to forfeit the construction trailer and all of it's contents to the victim.  No contact with victim.  Follow through with AODA treatment/counseling if deemed appropriate by Agent.  Defendant not to work as a general contractor.  Court would consider lifting this condition if defendant attends appropriate schooling.  
CONDITION TIME: 90 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS -STAYED for use by Agent.
